This is a Python client for the Google Buzz API.

The directory structure is organized as follows:
buzz.py - the Python module containing the Buzz API client
README - this file
docs - documentatation generated from the code using epydoc
examples - which contains examples showing how to use this client to manipulate the Buzz API
third_party - which contains the various libraries that buzz.py depends upon


Documentation is generated using epydoc: http://epydoc.sourceforge.net/
The command we're currently using is:
epydoc buzz.py -o docs
